					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>Inscribed fragment recovered from the excavation site No. 7.</p>						

						<p>Undated. Palaeographically datable to the Brāhmī of 3rd century A.D. Written in the Prākṛit language.</p>						

						<p>Refers to the payment of a <hi rend="italic">dīnāra-māshaka</hi> for maintaining an endowment for the feeding and clothing, apparently of monks. Mentions Kalūra [and Buddhist sect <hi rend="italic">apara-mahā-sēliya?</hi>].</p>						

						</summary>
